                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-09-28</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is one of the better Wrox Handbooks and I really liked it.  This isn't exactly a guide beginners guide on class design, nor is it an experts book..but it does one thing very well, if you are new to VB.NET or .NET and you know what you want your classes to do, this book will show you how to accomplish it.  Moreover, there are some good examples and it can get you thinking in different directions.<p>They were a little skimpy on issues like using Properties vs. Public Variables (and if you move to .NET, you will have to fight VB6 programmers clinging on to bad habits of the past), but overall, I think the book does a great job at what it advertises itself to be.<p>Also, the discussion on Delegates and event handling was particularly helpful if that's your interest.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">excellent book</div>
